==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Absolutism
<hw>Ab"so*lu`tism</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The state of being absolute; the system or doctrine of the
absolute; the principles or practice of absolute or arbitrary
government; despotism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The element of <qex>absolutism</qex> and prelacy was
controlling.</q> <rj><qau>Palfrey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Theol.)</fld> <def>Doctrine of absolute
decrees.</def> <rj><au>Ash.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Absolutist</ent>⟦br⟧
